<font color="#FF0000">FRIENDS OF FREEDOM</font><br>
<tt>Wed Feb 11  0:13:20 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
&quot;Friends of Freedom&quot;<br><br>
Stalwarts have fallen and cravens have died, <br>
consumed by a common, treacherous tide<br>
that rolls, crimson,  onto freedom's shore.<br><br>
Some were mocking, while others cried, <br>
all clutched in fierce battle, side by side<br>
protecting  freedom's battered door.<br><br>
There were those who quit, some who tried,<br>
some were sparred life and many denied<br>
in the harsh, final tally of freedom's score.<br><br>
But all who limped away with the broken stride <br>
past the lazy slacker's and the coward's chide<br>
remain Freedom's shunned heros, forevermore.<br><br>
Their broken, wounded spirits still feigh and hide<br>
clutching at lost brothers for a forgotten pride<br>
And, only Freedom knows the burdens they bore.<br><br>
